In German, the "merged" activity reads really bad:

!pr-notification-action.png!

For English speakers: It's like it would read "Kristy the pull request MERGED".

The problem is this in {{email-pull-request-batch.soy}} and {{email-pull-request.soy}}:

{code}
{$lozengeContent|noAutoescape} {{getText('stash.email.pull-request.the-pull-request')}}
{code}

This assumes that the word order is always the same: ACTION the pull request. In languages other than English, this doesn't work. The string should be split into multiple strings (for each action) and contain a placeholder for the lozenge.

When trying to acccess the Atlassian Git LFS server with *batch mode disabled*, that is in .git/config there is a line
{noformat}
[lfs]
  batch = false
{noformat}
, JWT authentication might fail with an error message like this:
{noformat}
Expecting claim 'qsh' to have value 'ae7000d663f8fd54188ee281c6cd2b993e14fc137edc388d08d983d4fba1cb72' but instead it has the value '2cc818a83a2278b909f968babd376ba9f710d9369c916f956f34b34a34c5e4e8'
{noformat}
Apparently the default for the batch option changed from git-lfs v0.52 to 0.60 (see https://github.com/github/git-lfs/blob/master/docs/api/http-v1-batch.md ). Due to this, this bug probably affects only old repositories that have the old default in their config or that specifically turned batch processing off.
Ideally Atlassians git-lfs implementation would implement both options. In case that's not feasible it would be helpful to have a better error message that gives a hint, that batch processing is not supported and the config should be changed.

In the Smart Mirror synchronization algorithm, if database level errors happen (e.g., a constraint violation if an update in response to a webhook event to the same repository is committed concurrently) then the entire transaction potentially including updates to a large number of repositories is rolled back.  This can be seen in the logs as errors of the form:

{noformat}
2016-04-24 02:51:21,287 ERROR [threadpool:thread-4]  c.a.b.i.m.m.s.DefaultMirrorSynchronizationHelper bitbucket (url=...): full synchronization failed
org.springframework.transaction.UnexpectedRollbackException: Transaction rolled back because it has been marked as rollback-only
{noformat}

This should be fixed so that transactions that fail due to concurrent updates only roll back a small number of updates, and that the full synchronization algorithm retries those updates after a short delay.

